{
  "texts": [
    "Integrating patient data into wearable devices launches a new era of health technology [66,67].",
    "Accordingly, several healthcare systems have incorporated devices that can connect wearable devices to EHRs.",
    "Integrating these new applications could increase patient data transparency and improve patient care quality [68,69].",
    "However, they lack system interoperability, cannot be easily integrated into EHR systems, and raise privacy concerns [66,67].",
    "Virtual Reality (VR) and Augmented Reality (AR)VR is defined as ''simulations that use various combinations of interaction between devices and sensory display systems'' [70]."
  ]
}